chunk_content: Age refers to age G reporting period at specimen collection Denominator: Calculated indicator, sum of: PMTCT_STAT POS: PMTCT_STAT_POS + HTS_TST_POS from the (1) Newly Tested Positive, (2) Known Positive at [PostANC1: Pregnancy/L&D] + [PostANC1: BF] entry (see PMTCT_STAT reference sheet for modalities (see PMTCT_STAT & HTS_TST reference more details) and (3) HTS_TST_POS: [PostANC1: sheets) Pregnancy/L&D] + [PostANC1: BF] modalities (see HTS_TST reference sheet for more details) Indicator changes • The numerator will now capture any virologic HIV test (sample collected) by 12 months of age, not (MER v2.6.1 to 2.7): just the first virologic test. • Two disaggregates were added (“first test” and “second or more test”). • Updated guiding narrative questions. Reporting level: Facility Reporting Quarterly frequency: How to use: This indicator measures the extent to which HIV-exposed infants receive a virologic HIV test to determine their HIV status by 12 months of age.
